<|startoftext|>My girlfriend and I decided to try the new spot we saw and love. A family owned place that seems like so many things.... but our first impression, was that the location looked like where the apartment was from a drive through. Well it's where I'm from and it's also a very cute, clean and simple location. When we're in Scottsdale, it's a must try! My girlfriend and I decided to share the chicken taco burrito on a Sunday and we loved it so much we ate it both. It comes with rice and beans. It wasn't heavy nor packed full of toppings. It's the kind of place that I can easily eat the food on my own and leave my partner feeling full. So, we ordered two burritos: one filled with rice and beans (the regular size) and one filled with a tortilla chip with salsa in it and a quacamie for dessert. We ordered the tacos at the drive through. The tortillas were fresh and flavorful. There weren't too many chips. They did have several types of beans. The burrito was a little small but the cilantro and red onions inside made it really easy to eat. The cilantro was fresh and peppery! It was delicious. I love that they let the workers do their make sure and they even have a camera where you can take pictures on your phone and send them to your friends. I think I'm excited to see how it tastes. It could very good. One thing I noticed is that the tortillas came in smaller sizes but if you like your food spicy please keep that in mind. There were lots of veggies in this burrito, but that was pretty small for a burrito. The lady at the counter explained that they had tried to keep this as a regular size and there was no way they could fit the fillings so they switched it to a small medium sized burrito. We were really hoping it tasted as flavorful as it was small. But it didn't so I can only give it a 2 star. I really recommend for anyone looking for a local hangout but this may be it for you.<|endoftext|>
